The paper discusses the security concerns in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of cryptography and network security (cs.CR). The focus of the paper is on the performance analysis of symmetric key ciphers, which is related to network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the resource constraints of the devices used in WSN, which is related to system and control theory (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
